# Component Structure Rules

- Components should be functional components
- Props should extend HTML element attributes (e.g., `extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>`)
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Keep components focused and small (like Button.tsx and Input.tsx)
- One component per file
- Use PascalCase for component file names
- Keep components in src/components
- Use proper TypeScript file extensions (.tsx) 